description:
&lt;p&gt;North Powys Older Persons Community Health Team is looking to recruit a Band 7 Mental Health Practitioner who is dedicated to the delivery of excellent care for the older adult with mental health difficulties, both those of a organic and functional need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will ensure the comprehensive provision of a cost effective,&lt;br /&gt;accessible, appropriate and responsive Community mental health Team&lt;br /&gt;(CMHT) service to service users with complex mental health needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will support the Older Persons Services Manager and Health Board/Local&lt;br /&gt;Authority personnel with the implementation of the Powys Dementia Plan&lt;br /&gt;Mental Health National Service Frameworks, underpinned by a person centred&lt;br /&gt;approach and develop policies and protocols to support the associated&lt;br /&gt;principals and values.&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will carry the continuing responsibility for the assessment,&lt;br /&gt;planning, implementation and evaluation of care needs and quality assurance.&lt;br /&gt;The Manager will develop and coordinate a multi-professional approach&lt;br /&gt;providing evidence based mental health care to all those who use the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameTeresa Morgan-JonesJob titleService Manager Older Peoples Team North PowysEmail addressteresa.morgan-jones@wales.nhs.ukTelephone number07966972845&lt;/p&gt;
